<Retconned>

Reposting some trivia on SO/PV:

Nocterrans generally have names that are taken from Egyptian myth and history, albeit chopped up and scrambled. Some are clearer than others, and some names are meaningful in some way. Not all of them, of course. For example, Siris (Osiris) is the father of Subina (Anubis). One exception is Fernetis' butler, Sejeve, whose name is an anagram of Jeeves because comedy.

As a bonus, Caithians are themes after old Fae lore. Toldrum is taken from one tale of the Cait Sith, and Niat is taken from Titania, queen of faeries.

/hm(a)ofa(h)/
